## ATT&CK Navigator

ATT&CK Navigator allows:

- Visual mapping of techniques
- Layer customisation
- Group-based attack analysis
- Detection coverage visualisation

SOC analysts use it to:

- Map alerts to techniques
- Identify defensive gaps
- Improve detection strategy

---

## ATT&CK in SOC Operations

SOC analysts use MITRE ATT&CK to:

- Classify incidents consistently
- Align alerts to known attacker behaviour
- Improve threat hunting queries
- Standardise reporting
- Enhance SIEM detection logic

Example:

Alert: Suspicious PowerShell activity  
Mapped To:
- Tactic: Execution
- Technique: Command and Scripting Interpreter (PowerShell)

---

## ATT&CK for Threat Intelligence

Threat intelligence teams use ATT&CK to:

- Profile adversary groups
- Track known techniques
- Understand campaign patterns
- Predict attacker behaviour

Example:

APT group known for:
- Spearphishing
- Credential dumping
- Registry persistence

SOC can proactively monitor those techniques.

---

## Cyber Analytics Repository (CAR)

CAR provides:

- Detection analytics mapped to ATT&CK techniques
- Query examples for SIEM
- Detection engineering references

Helps SOC teams design better monitoring rules.

---

## MITRE D3FEND

D3FEND complements ATT&CK by mapping defensive techniques to offensive techniques.

Purpose:

- Connect defensive controls to attacker behaviour
- Improve mitigation strategy

---

## SOC Investigation Example

Scenario:

User opens malicious email attachment.

Mapping:

Initial Access → Spearphishing Attachment  
Execution → PowerShell  
Persistence → Registry Run Keys  
Command & Control → Beaconing traffic  
Exfiltration → Data transfer

MITRE helps track the full attacker lifecycle.

